CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 7, 1974, pg. 22, reads: "Keeping People Informed - The Militant Bookstore on 3400 Fifth Ave., offers readers some different literature they can't get at other places. The store hopes to expand and offer people even a larger selection in near future. - (Harris Photo)"
TitMainTitle: Woman wearing bell bottoms and head scarf, reading "The Life and Times of Frederick Douglas" in Militant Bookstore, 3400 Fifth Avenue
